comments.comment: Windows 10; Tensorflow 1.14.0 I sucessfully convert the model to a PB file and TFLite file. But exactly the OP: tf.image.crop_and_resize was not support when using tf.lite.Interpreter Is there any solution or alternatives? tf.image.crop_and_resize seems extremely important when implement Mask RCNN!

<denchmark-link:https://github.com/Zhuxinpei>@Zhuxinpei</denchmark-link>
Can you please refer to <denchmark-link:https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/issues/24407#issuecomment-650140464>this comment</denchmark-link> and let us know. Please provide with complete stand alone code,and error log, please try on 2.x as we officially support 2.x and let us know if the issue persist on 2.x.

I still can not convert the tf.image.crop_and_resize op to TFlite in tf-2.3.0 and tf-nighly-20201023. The demo code as follow: <denchmark-code>import tensorflow as tf
@tf.function def roiAlign(feature, select_bbox): roi_feature = tf.image.crop_and_resize(feature, select_bbox, box_indices=[0], crop_size=[7, 7]) return roi_feature
feature = tf.random.normal(shape=[1, 14, 14, 32]) select_bbox = tf.constant([[0.1, 0.1, 0.6, 0.6]], dtype=tf.float32) concrete_func = roiAlign.get_concrete_function(feature, select_bbox)
converter = tf.lite.TFLiteConverter.from_concrete_functions([concrete_func]) tflite_model = converter.convert() </denchmark-code>
